observations.recommendation:
We recommended that:
1. The Local Chief Executive (LCE) designate a responsible official to facilitate the processing of the Certificate of Title of the 33 parcels of land owned by the Municipality in order to establish absolute ownership and protect the interest of the Municipality;
2. Create an Appraisal Committee composed of the Municipal Assessor, Engineer, and Treasurer to facilitate the appraisal of the value of the parcels of land owned by the Municipality;
3. Direct the Municipal Accountant to make the necessary adjusting entries to recognize the parcels of land in the book of accounts based on the data gathered by the Appraisal Committee and start maintaining the Land and Land Improvements Ledger Card and Subsidiary Ledger to each lot/land classified as land and land improvement. The Accounting Staff in charge of maintaining this ledger shall record promptly the acquisition, description, impairment, disposal, and other information about the land/lot property; and
4. Direct the General Services Officer to start maintaining the Land and Land Improvements Property Card for each property classified as land and land improvement. The Staff in charge of maintaining the card shall record promptly the acquisition, description, disposal, and other information about the land and land improvement.

We recommended and management agreed that the Local Chief Executive direct: 

1.	The Municipal Treasurer to:

a.	Ensure accuracy and completeness in the preparation of the Check Register and Report of Checks Issued for each fund in accordance with Sections 42 and 43 of Chapter 3 of the NGAS Manual for LGUs;

We recommended and management agreed that the Local Chief Executive direct the:

1.	MDRRM Officer and Other Persons Responsible to:

a)    Ensure that expenses that are administrative in nature shall be charged against the appropriations for the MDRRM Office and use the fund prudently;

We recommended that the LCE direct the responsible/concerned department heads to do the following (based on the guidelines prescribed by COA Circular No. 2018-002):

Secure directly from the GSIS GIF, all insurances or bonds covering properties, contracts, rights of action, and other insurable risks of their respective offices;
Prepare the Property Inventory Form (PIF) listing of the insurable properties and other assets, showing their latest appraised values/valuation, appraised date, location, and other information;
Extract from the Report on the Physical Count of PPE the data for the PIF pertaining to the insurable assets and interest of the government;
Cause the appraisal of the insurable properties and other assets of their respective offices;
Submit the consolidated PIF to the Office of the Auditor and the GIF, GSIS, not later than April 30 of each year; 
Include in the annual appropriation the amount of premiums for the general insurance covering all insurable assets and other assets and ensure its payment to the GSIS; and
Ensure centralized payment of insurance premiums to avoid double payment.

The Acting Municipal Treasurer to: 
See to it that Collections on hand are deposited daily or not later than the next banking day;
Issue demand for those Collectors with under remittance;
Issue letter of authority to the Barangay Treasurer as deputized collector and request prompt turnover of collections to the Designated Liquidating Officer; and 
Formulate policies and procedures in the issuance of the accountable forms to the collectors, period of remittance in accordance with the Local Treasury Operations Manual and proper reporting of collections/ remittance/deposits and accountable forms received and issued in the Reports of Collections and Deposits/Remittances.

We recommended that the LCE direct the:

LDRRM Officer and Other Persons Responsible to:

Ensure that the administrative expenses shall be charged against the appropriations for LDRRM Office, not against LDRRM Funds, and use the funds prudently;
Avoid charging non-allowable expenses against the LDRRM Fund in order to avoid audit suspensions/ disallowances;
Submit all the Disbursement Vouchers (DVs) for expenses charged against the LDRRMF. Audit suspensions or disallowances will be issued if none is submitted;
Submit the lacking supporting documents of the submitted DVs. Audit suspensions or disallowances will be issued if none is submitted; and
Inform the Chairman and Board of Directors of the Balasan Water District to refund all of their claims from the Municipal Government that were charged against the LDRRMF. Submit copy of the settlements to the Office of the Auditor. Audit suspensions or disallowances will be issued if none is submitted.

