Create an Appraisal Committee composed of the Municipal Assessor, Engineer, and Treasurer to facilitate the appraisal of the value of the parcels of land owned by the Municipality;
Direct the Municipal Accountant to make the necessary adjusting entries to recognize the parcels of land in the book of accounts based on the data gathered by the Appraisal Committee and start maintaining the Land and Land Improvements Ledger Card and Subsidiary Ledger to each lot/land classified as land and land improvement. The Accounting Staff in charge of maintaining this ledger shall record promptly the acquisition, description, impairment, disposal, and other information about the land/lot property; and
Direct the General Services Officer to start maintaining the Land and Land Improvements Property Card for each property classified as land and land improvement. The Staff in charge of maintaining the card shall record promptly the acquisition, description, disposal, and other information about the land and land improvement.

