The LCE to direct the persons responsible to draft a budgetary proposal for the appropriation of personal services, mooe and capital outlay of the MDRRM Office in order to avoid charging of the same to the 5% MDRRMF;
MDRRMO to only charge expenses in the 5% MDRRMF that are related/connected to the implementation of the 5% programs/projects/activities;
Persons responsible to attach complete supporting documents to each and every claim for easy evaluation of the correctness and propriety of the same; and
OIC-Municipal Accountant to double check completeness and propriety of supporting documents before payment.

We recommended that the LCE direct the:
MDRRMO to double check the declared current appropriation of the 30% QRF and Mitigation Fund, continuing appropriation and the Previous Year’s  Appropriation transferred to the Special Trust Fund;
MDRRMO and OIC-Municipal Accountant to reconcile the records on hand and present the correct balance of the unutilized MDRRMF in the Report on Utilization and Notes to the FS and submit the same to the Office of the Auditor;
OIC-Municipal Accountant to include a discussion on the details of the unexpended balances of the MDRRMF in the Notes to the FS as required in Annex D of COA Circular No. 2012-002.

We recommended the following:
The LCE to create the Gender and Development Focal Point System (GFPS) in compliance with Item A, Section 4 of JMC No. 2013-01 and ensure that all members of the Local GFPS including the elected local officials and department heads undergo capacity building programs on GAD;
Persons responsible to allocate/mainstream/correspond at least 5% of the Municipality approved budget to activities that will support implementation of GAD programs/projects/activities (PPAs) that will address both client and organization-focused gender issues. Also, to be mindful of the expenses that are to be charged under the GAD fund in order to avoid future audit suspensions/disallowances;
GAD focal person to coordinate with the MPDO to set up a comprehensive GAD database which will serve as the basis for gender-responsive planning, programming and policy formulation.

We recommended that the LCE:
Request the Sangguniang Bayan of Balasan, Iloilo to pass an ordinance legally creating the existing public utilities and other economic enterprises as Local Economic Enterprises (LEEs);
Direct the preparation of a 5-year Staffing Plan and Staff Transition pursuant to Section 5.2 of the Manual;
Assign responsible personnel to develop a detailed 5-Year Business Plan (BP) for the LEE. The BP shall cover all facets of the LEEs operations including management, operations, staffing, risk analysis, marketing and sales. Appendix A of the same Manual shows a detailed outline for a BP that follows the requirements of commercial and development financing institutions;
Direct the person in-charge to:
Present the 5-Year Business Plan and stress the importance of directing the LEE operations towards self-sufficiency; and
Review and assess the LEEs five years after instituting changes to comply with the legal provisions governing such. Review and assessment activities will help the Municipality determine whether to continue, modify, expand, scale down or close the LEE operations. Section 7 of the same Manual provides the guidelines in assessing whether the LEEs are viable and shall continue to operate or not.

