We recommended the following:
The LCE to direct the creation of an Inventory Committee, since inventory taking is an indispensable procedure for checking the propriety of property custodianship;
The GSO to prepare procedures on the conduct of physical inventory of PPE and present such to the Agency Head for approval;
The Inventory Committee, with the GSO as one of the members, to develop a plan to include a timeline for the physical inventory, who will supervise the count, the personnel to act as counters and checkers, and the sequence of the counting. A set of written instructions shall be prepared to be observed by each person connected with the inventory-taking. For furniture and fixtures, equipment and the like, inventory tags should be serially pre-numbered and prepared in duplicate with a perforation separating the top and bottom portions of the tag;
