Based on the information gathered in procedure no. 4, determine if accounting records and property records were prepared for these PPEs. If there were none, the Municipal Accountant and GSO shall create a PPELC and PC for each PPE as discussed above. PPE without accounting records should be properly disclosed;
For the current purchases of PPE, the Municipal Accountant and GSO immediately prepare the PPELC and PC, respectively and issue the corresponding Acknowledgement Receipt for Equipment (ARE) to the accountable employee;
Submit the Report on physical inventory as required by regulations;
The Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the GSO with the complete data, description and cost segregation of road components for the road projects;
The Municipal Accountant to prepare a Journal Entry Voucher to record the required initial recognition of 25% of Local Road Network and its component in the General Ledger based on the available data in the Registry of Public Infrastructures; and
Prepare the corresponding Local Road Network Card presented as Annex D of the above COA Circular; maintain subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network; and prepare a schedule for the computation of depreciation for each component at the end of the year.

Recommendations:
We recommended the following:
The Municipal Assessor to provide a copy of an updated Assessment Roll to the Municipal Treasurer;
The Municipal Treasurer to update the RPT Account Register/Taxpayer’s index card based on the Assessment Roll and furnish the Municipal Accountant a duly certified list showing the names of taxpayers and the amount due and collectible for the year;
Based on the list, the Municipal Accountant to draw a JEV to record the debit to RPT/SET Receivables and credit to Deferred RPT/SET Income; and
The Municipal Accountant to reconcile recordings involving RPT/SET transactions and make necessary correcting/adjusting entries.

Recommendations:
We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the꞉
Municipal Treasurer to request for snapshot bank statements every time they have transactions at the Authorized Government Depository Bank (AGDB) of the LGU to facilitate prompt reconciliation of book and bank balances;
Municipal Treasurer to submit the RCDs pertaining to the above-mentioned items for adjustments as cited by the Municipal Accountant in her reply;
Municipal Treasurer to verify the validation of deposit slips of the recorded debits to Cash in Bank-LCCA account amounting to P23,543.00  in the books but were not credited in the bank account. Send a letter request, with deposit slips attached, to the AGDB of the LGU that the deposits be recognized as valid credits to the account. Otherwise, if there were no deposits made, the Municipal Treasurer should charge the amount to the responsible Accountable Officer; and
Municipal Accountant to take up immediately all valid reconciling items requiring adjustment in the books of the LGU including the reversion of the amount of stale checks to the Cash in Bank – LCCA and the setting up of the corresponding Accounts Payable as provided in Item 1.4 b) and c), Section 83 (b) of the DOF-BLGF Local Operations Manual.

Recommendations:
We recommended the following:
The Assist. Municipal Treasurer together with the persons responsible to submit the payrolls indicated in the attached documents for the 1st and 2nd releases and supporting documents mentioned in Section 5.1.4 of DSWD MC No. 4, Series of 2015;
As an alternative, due to the volume of documents, the submitted payrolls shall be supported with a checklist certified correct by the school heads and verified correct by the MSWDO, confirming the qualifications of student beneficiaries as prescribed in Section 5.1.4 of the said Memorandum Circular. Documents detailing and authenticating the qualifications and entitlement of beneficiaries to the Educational Assistance shall be kept in the Office of the MSWDO and made available for audit at any given time;
The MSWDO, from now on, to attach the essential documents before drawing a Cash Advance; and
The Municipal Accountant to double check the supporting documents before processing the Cash Advance for a legally specific purpose; and recheck the liquidation documents before booking up and submitting the same to the Office of the Auditor.  Henceforth, documents supporting the CA and those in support of its liquidation shall be separately identified.

